    "body": "'spack install boost' fails trying to run 'b2 --clean' :  b2 was built with back-end instructions and so fails with \r\n\r\n```\r\n ./b2 --clean   \r\n[1]    57337 illegal hardware instruction (core dumped)  ./b2 --clean\r\n```\r\nmy default environment uses the intel compilers, though 'spack spec' suggests things are built with gcc-6.3.\r\n\r\nI do not see a way to ask spack to tell boost to use \"toolset=cray\".  (was trying to follow advice found in https://cug.org/proceedings/cug2016_proceedings/includes/files/pap127.pdf , which did seem to work for a non-spack build)",
